			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Agro for tanking purposes...<a name="71983"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 10 05 3:31 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>How can I get it? Bards aren't usually (ever?) main tanks, but I've definitely been in groups where I've been the highest hp/ac character... I've tried several strategies and none of them seem to work.
<br />
 
<br />
Debuffing/HOS/ROT on the mob that I pulled WHILE it is inc (pulled by me of course) seem to do nothing, or at least too little to keep a shammy from pulling agro. Even if I somehow get aggro back, twisting the classic songs (mana, nuke/overhaste, warsong) and either Largo's or Zurikis (new aoe dot/slow) don't seem to add much agro.  Shield of songs (the old rune song) did less for me than Zurikis did, despite some posts I read about its agro.
<br />

<br />
My two attempts to tank in higher level zones were not too great using those strategies. I only held agro well enough to be considered the tank in a pickup group that had a maximum level of 66 excluding me, the 70 bard (ele equipped at the time, I believe the others were there or below). The other time, I was with a guild group, debuff/HOS/ROTed on inc and snared as my 4th twist.  The shammy slowed, immediately pulled agro, and actually kited the mob around the room while I attacked it at melee range, twisting constantly.  I think I got agro back at 60%, then lost it to the ranger when he snared.  Next mob, cleric pulled agro, died, then the ranger pulled agro, died, and then the rogue pulled agro until i mezzed the mob for a breather.
<br />

<br />
So I'm putting the group tank idea on hold for now.  What songs are best, and would they work if they were resisted? I havent tested mez because the tank has pulled agro perfectly fine when I had a mob mezzed for five minutes.  Would the new snare work better for pulling agro because it has a longer duration? Would an unsuccessful charm work (I need to not burn all my mana if tanking and would want to use a lower level song) if I used the 12 second or 60 second mana charm (on mobs 63-68)? Would fear, also autoresisted at highlevels, give any kind of agro? Does a resisted song give as much agro as if the song actually lands? Any answers, even if they are negative (which I think is probably the case) would be greatly appreciated</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
