				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Agro for tanking purposes...<a name="71985"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 10 05 7:34 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Every single pick up group I have been in, i have had more hps and more ac then the tanks that join.  I seen tanks with 10k hp buffed try to come into RS thinking they can tank.  They are such mana drains for healers.  I have tried tanking myself and the only way I can do it is if mobs are rooted and I use close proximity aggro.  But even then it still bounces around.  Also when I pull I have the healer throw me a non aggro heal when I need it and hit it for a bit.  Then the others join in.  I havent tried with anger proccing weapons, but I think that may work too.  I really do think bards need a way to hold aggro since we are a plate hybrid and all hybrids have some way to hold aggro.  h*ll even clerics can hold aggro.  Many times especially late night grouping no tanks or healers can be found.  With the low population of players it makes it even harder.  Would be nice to be able to fill that tank void if needed.
<br />

<br />
Conaden Darksong, 70 Bard
<br />
Tholuxe</span></td>
