				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Agro for tanking purposes...<a name="72007"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 10 05 3:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I think its impossible. Why? Well heres a little anecdote to illustrate my point.
<br />

<br />
I'm level 68 and haven't done my Remove Curse and Remove Poison song quests yet, so I headed over to Dulak. There was a poor 47 Wizard at zone LFG for about 10 mins so I invited for some XP while I meleed down greenies for my quest item. Yes he got xp amazingly.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I'm using 18 and 19 delay weapons, both of which have 2 procs. I have 42% worn haste, and I'm twisting Warmarch of the Muram, Shurikis Shenanigans (AOE dot/slow), and mana/heal song. So basically I am beating the h*ll out of these greenies.
<br />

<br />
The 47 wiz nukes for 600 when the green mob is at 40% health and guess what - INSTA aggro. So basically we cant even hold aggro over a 47 wizard after slowing, dotting, and meleeing a mob down to 40% health.
<br />

<br />
Anger procs are probably the only answer, but is there any cheap droppable ones? A bard will never be allowed an anger proc weapon on a raid, the BOC is like 200k so have fun buying that. Maybe LDON augs? I wouldnt spend that many LODN points on an anger aug since I would so rarely use it.</span></td>
