				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Agro for tanking purposes...<a name="72008"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 10 05 4:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Several threads on the concert hall about this.
<br />

<br />
Basic answer is that the group needs to know you have no snap aggro so they must control themselves. You will need to pull and make sure it is slowed then use your chants and dps to gain aggro (bellow when you can as it helps). The better your weapons the better your aggro. A BoC is best unless you are time enabled then an edge is as good or better. People mention using a shield or intimidation but I have not found that to work for me. I can tank MPG and below just fine if the slower doesnt try to slow until the mob is at 95% and the rogue starts in at 90%. My wiz can nuke twice starting at 60% and 40%. So a bard can tank.
<br />

<br />
I think your problem with the wiz up above is a level issue. Your songs (other then shenanigans) are very low aggro but your dps should have enough aggro to handle a 600 pt nuke, so I can only assume the AI sees this low level wiz and decides to take them out. You see this type of huge aggro with things like root/sitting/undead/low health.
<br />

<br />
P.s. Anger procs are Warrior only - best bet is dd/stun types</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
