				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Agro for tanking purposes...<a name="72009"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 10 05 5:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just qant to say 2 thing.
<br />

<br />
1) if you dont have a BoC and WA5, forget it.
<br />
2) BoC &gt;&gt;&gt; EoE for aggro generation, I have both, and i can tell your there no way in h*ll the EoE can sustain the aggro BoC proc generate <u>for bards</u>. For any other class its completly different. 
<br />

<br />
The difference is Bards got an innate aggro calcul that reduce the aggro of anything we do. And this include procs. For a mysterious reason, the proc that are pure raw Aggro (like BoC, Anger, etc..) are bypassing that reduction.
<br />

<br />
On a side note, I recently put a 125 ykesha proc on my BoC and didnt tested it yet.. I hope it help..</span></td>
