				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree, Snasty.  I prefer the consistant agro of EOE in primary.  I put ykesha augs in both the EOE and BOC, so those help a little.  Maxed WA, ambidexterity and Harmonious attack.  My song line up goes like this:
<br />

<br />
Pull with:
<br />

<br />
HOS/Exhultant bellow
<br />
ROT
<br />
DoT (or two, depending how long the pull)
<br />
Level 51 snare/slow (time it to land about when mob hits camp).
<br />

<br />
Tank for at least 20 seconds with no slows/heals or assists to build agro.
<br />

<br />
Twist:
<br />
DoT
<br />
DoT
<br />
Marr
<br />
HoS
<br />

<br />
Let the slower slow at about 90% (I've slowed it for 57% already so no big deal), and try to avoid grouping with rogues at all, as they own bard agro, lol.
<br />

<br />
So, this works ok, up to about WoS for me.  I haven't really had the nerve to try it in MPG yet.  Maybe once I get all of the new OOW mitigation AA <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />.</span></td>
