				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Agro for tanking purposes...<a name="72372"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 24 05 12:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, so you really really want aggro, hunh? Well I found 2 ways to get it , that actually work !!!!! A
<br />

<br />
<u>Method #1</u>
<br />
<span class="Highlight">DA+Dance of the Blade</span>
<br />

<br />
Ok, lets say your crappy tank takes a nose dive and the mob is running around pounding the tar outta the other group members higher on the aggro list than you. Well, in this case sing group DA, then click your own off, and attack the mob, and hit your riposte disc. The DA will drop the group lower on the aggro list, and gives you 18 seconds to build up your aggro. Its not as good as the second method below, but the groups more likely to survive this way. **Note: In emergencies, use method 1 &amp; 2 together to help buid your aggro.
<br />

<br />
<u>Method #2</u>
<br />
<span class="Highlight">Spam Shield of Songs </span>
<br />
Lets say that you decide you want to be main tank for your group cause the MT has less HP/AC/Def AA's than you do. Well heres the fun part....Remember that old school song &quot;Shield of Songs&quot; ? Well this seems to be the only honest aggro song we have. Probably a bug/glitch but it works, so use it. You cant twist a bunch of crap and SoS and maintain aggro...You just SPAM sos, over &amp; over &amp; over. I thought someone was pulling my leg when they told me about this, but ive used it in MPG and PoP and it works surprisingly well.
<br />

<br />
Ok, good luck being a tank.....I just pray you have at least the PoP defensive AA's. </span></td>
