				<td colspan="2"><span>Copied and pasted this from Concert Hall:
<br />

<br />

<br />
Greetings Concert Hall.
<br />

<br />
Long time reader first time poster. My name is Xeib and I am the QA lead for EverQuest. I played a bard on Test Server for quite some time. I may not be as experienced as many of you, but I have a great deal of respect for many of the bards that frequent this forum. Many times as a player I visited the Concert Hall looking for sage advice on quests, skills and songs. I was rarely dissappointed
<br />

<br />
It took me a bit of time to figure out what was happening with bard chant aggro, and what wasn't happening (that should have been) I apoligize that it took me so long to get it all puzzled out)
<br />

<br />
The fix went to Test Server today and passed. You can expect me to still be lurking here , and posting rarely. I come to the concert hall now to find Bard bugs, so please don't hesitate to post bard bugs here. I will look for them here. 
<br />

<br />
Here is a bit of background on me in case you care.
<br />

<br />
I played Everquest initially as a necromancer up until Kunark release. Later I was bored and tried many of the classes EverQuest has to offer. I found my home playing a bard.
<br />

<br />
Playing a bard is so much different than any other class. Not only does it require sacrifice from the player (you cant talk much or you send tells with 11 22 55 66 etc. ) but It requires split second decisions, to switch songs when you know something else is needed by the group, to do CC when your enchanter is going to get munched, and oftentimes to just sit silent and take the blame when things go bad (not like its our fault  ) I loved the class, and it prolonged my playing of EverQuest for quite some time.
<br />

<br />
I have a great respect for the bards of EverQuest (I can even appreciate Liq style commentary)
<br />

<br />
I will be around as much as Grumbuk, and Rytan is and if the need is great, please do not hesitate to log on to test and send me a tell with in-game issues
<br />

<br />
Xeib-QA 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Then Gumbak responds:
<br />

<br />
The bug was the result of instrument modifiers not yet being calculated into the damage value at the time the hate was being applied. I didn't find or make this fix but I knew it was important enough to folks to ask about it, so there you have it. Sorry it took so long to identify.
<br />

<br />
Cheers
<br />
</span></td>
