				<td colspan="2"><span>For certain, the hate procs/aggro weapons that were available at the DoN mission camps would be a great help to bard aggro if they remain that way.  Personally I hope the class listings on them was a mistake and that they'll be changed to warrior only. 
<br />

<br />
Even then though, from the bit of playing around with tanking that I've done, weapon damage and procs alone don't do it. No, the aggro from the chants is definitely needed as well. I think that now the aggro per HP of damage on a dot that we get is on par with that which shamans get. Perhaps even higher aggro for the poison chant or the like. Either way, I found that it's not bad to maintain aggro if, as someone said before, the group is careful about it. Even if the rest of the group has very good DPS, going to three or four chants (and keeping fufil's diminishing dirge on it) allows maintaining aggro pretty well, at least for a class that isn't really meant to be a tank.</span></td>
