				<td colspan="2"><span>Upon further testing, using two dots and grouping with a rogue that assisted immediately seemed to hold agro maybe 75% of the time... we had the same offhand and my primary was 26/20 w/ 125 dd proc, his primary was rogue epic at i believe 21/20.  Getting the casters to not nuke/snare right away like idiots can be tough, but it is possible, even if people laugh at you at first.  I don't understand the obsession with Eoe that everyone has, a high dps weapon + dots is what seems to matter.  1 dot holds agro over most casters that nuke somewhat late, 2 dots holds agro over most melee, 3 dots i hate to use because i lose warsong but that holds agro quite well... if you have a good percussion mod.  Agro/stun procs don't really seem necessary, and who wants to rely on chance agro anyway...
<br />

<br />
Lots of spot heals will probably pull agro and are an exception, so its worth it to do max dottage on nameds i think, havent tried it in mpg yet tho.</span></td>
