				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Agro for tanking purposes...<a name="74205"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 9 05 4:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The rare times that I tank, I definitely use 3 dots minimum, along with my Muramite War Drum (3.0 modifier). I've found if I use 2 dots, and try the haste/regen added twists, I don't hold agro as well as the 3 dots/regen twist setup. I put my epic in my off-hand to get the occasional haste proc to give me some form of haste at least. I may not melee for a ton, but with my OOW Dots, doing 180+/tic on each dot, with the occasional 366/tic crit (crit AA's for dots maxed as well), as long as my group gives me a couple ticks, I can hold agro without too many problems. The times I can't are when I have multi pulls and get stuck putting a mob on mez. If your group members are used to having Paly's tank, and they rarely if ever have a bard tank, you got to lay out the rules so you can set yourself up for tanking success. Not everyone is aware that agro is a 2-way street, especially with a bard tanking.
<br />

<br />
Mooriss Flye
<br />
68th Bard
